image/169707/b6ca4efe-c3a1-4227-8444-97b26bf62220.jpeg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"\u003e\n      \u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003ca href=\"/opensauced/semantic-release-to-npm-andor-ghcr-without-any-tooling-5730\" class=\"ltag__link__link\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv class=\"ltag__link__content\"\u003e\n      \u003ch2\u003eSemantic release to npm and/or ghcr without any tooling\u003c/h2\u003e\n      \u003ch3\u003eTED Vortex (Teodor Eugen Duțulescu) for Open Sauced ・ Dec 7 ・ 7 min read\u003c/h3\u003e\n      \u003cdiv class=\"ltag__link__taglist\"\u003e\n        \u003cspan class=\"ltag__link__tag\"\u003e#actionshackathon21\u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan class=\"ltag__link__tag\"\u003e#github\u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan class=\"ltag__link__tag\"\u003e#docker\u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan class=\"ltag__link__tag\"\u003e#node\u003c/span\u003e\n      \u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"ltag__link\"\u003e\n  \u003ca href=\"/opensauced\" class=\"ltag__link__link\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv class=\"ltag__link__org__pic\"\u003e\n      \u003cimg src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/practicaldev/image/fetch/s--yXaV_lxN--/c_limit%2Cf_auto%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto%2Cw_880/https://res.cloudinary.com/practicaldev/image/fetch/s--8NGaZ5Fe--/c_fill%2Cf_auto%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_150%2Cq_auto%2Cw_150/https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/organization/profile_image/2498/ddb0e6e0-c659-4716-b066-8d42eb15cacd.png\" alt=\"Open Sauced\" loading=\"lazy\"\u003e\n      \u003cdiv class=\"ltag__link__user__pic\"\u003e\n        \u003cimg src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/practicaldev/image/fetch/s--gR8johnm--/c_limit%2Cf_auto%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto%2Cw_880/https://res.cloudinary.com/practicaldev/image/fetch/s--xu3ycHCE--/c_fill%2Cf_auto%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_150%2Cq_auto%2Cw_150/https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/user/profile_image/169707/b6ca4efe-c3a1-4227-8444-97b26bf62220.jpeg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"\u003e\n      \u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003ca href=\"/opensauced/automatically-update-git-major-tags-on-github-marketplace-release-1mgk\" class=\"ltag__link__link\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv class=\"ltag__link__content\"\u003e\n      \u003ch2\u003eAutomatically update git major tags on GitHub marketplace release\u003c/h2\u003e\n      \u003ch3\u003eTED Vortex (Teodor Eugen Duțulescu) for Open Sauced ・ Dec 7 ・ 2 min read\u003c/h3\u003e\n      \u003cdiv class=\"ltag__link__taglist\"\u003e\n        \u003cspan class=\"ltag__link__tag\"\u003e#actionshackathon21\u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan class=\"ltag__link__tag\"\u003e#github\u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan class=\"ltag__link__tag\"\u003e#actions\u003c/span\u003e\n      \u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"TED Vortex (Teodor Eugen Duțulescu)","url":"https://dev.to/0vortex"},"datePublished":"2021-12-07T08:24:09Z","dateModified":"2021-12-07T08:24:09Z","url":"https://dev.to/0vortex/comment/1kajf","interactionStatistic":[{"@type":"InteractionCounter","interactionType":"https://schema.org/LikeAction","userInteractionCount":2}],"comment":[{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-815949","text":"\u003cp\u003eThey look eligible to me! Great work!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Rizèl Scarlett","url":"https://dev.to/blackgirlbytes"},"datePublished":"2021-12-07T15:16:51Z","dateModified":"2021-12-07T15:16:51Z","url":"https://dev.to/blackgirlbytes/comment/1kb0h","interactionStatistic":[{"@type":"InteractionCounter","interactionType":"https://schema.org/LikeAction","userInteractionCount":2}],"parentItem":{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-815765"}}]},{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-808052","text":"\u003cp\u003eHi \u003ca class=\"mentioned-user\" href=\"https://dev.to/blackgirlbytes\"\u003e@blackgirlbytes\u003c/a\u003e\n and \u003ca class=\"mentioned-user\" href=\"https://dev.to/mishmanners\"\u003e@mishmanners\u003c/a\u003e\n \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eI have a technical question regarding GitHub Actions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIs it applicable to cache checkout actions?\u003cbr\u003e\nI mean, if I use multiple workflows that do require to checkout my repository, should I apply the same process each and every time I execute any of these workflows or does the cache action provide any alternative?\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eI know that caching the checkout isn't the right approach as we do need a new and clean version of the repository after each and every commit, but I also do think that cloning the same repository at each workflow is a little bit time consuming and doesn't make sense. So, what I'm really searching for is a way to only apply checkout once across multiple workflows and load the checkout out directory whenever needed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eI did some research on this topic but I found nothing except this unanswered discussion:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/actions/checkout/discussions/259\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003egithub.com/actions/checkout/discus...\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAny help would be appreciated...\u003c/p\u003e\n\n","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Shehab Hosny","url":"https://dev.to/shehab7osny"},"datePublished":"2021-11-20T05:51:29Z","dateModified":"2021-11-20T05:51:29Z","url":"https://dev.to/shehab7osny/comment/1jp8o","interactionStatistic":[{"@type":"InteractionCounter","interactionType":"https://schema.org/LikeAction","userInteractionCount":1}],"comment":[{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-812300","text":"\u003cp\u003eHey \u003ca class=\"mentioned-user\" href=\"https://dev.to/shehab7osny\"\u003e@shehab7osny\u003c/a\u003e\n!  \u003ca class=\"mentioned-user\" href=\"https://dev.to/mishmanners\"\u003e@mishmanners\u003c/a\u003e\n and I did a bit of research, and it looks like for the source code itself we would generally recommend the checkout is most appropriate. By default, it only pulls the latest commit rather than full history so the amount of data being transferred is already reasonably low. You can save significant time by enabling dependency caching when setting up your environment (such as Node or Python). See the relevant setup action (such as \u003ca href=\"https://github.blog/changelog/2021-07-02-github-actions-setup-node-now-supports-dependency-caching/\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003egithub.blog/changelog/2021-07-02-g...\u003c/a\u003e) and look for the ‘cache:’ attribute. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Rizèl Scarlett","url":"https://dev.to/blackgirlbytes"},"datePublished":"2021-11-29T23:41:08Z","dateModified":"2021-11-29T23:48:58Z","url":"https://dev.to/blackgirlbytes/comment/1k5g8","interactionStatistic":[{"@type":"InteractionCounter","interactionType":"https://schema.org/LikeAction","userInteractionCount":2}],"parentItem":{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-808052"}},{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-811816","text":"\u003cp\u003eI'm checking in on this and will be back to you soon 😄\u003c/p\u003e\n\n","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Michelle Duke","url":"https://dev.to/mishmanners"},"datePublished":"2021-11-29T00:18:44Z","dateModified":"2021-11-29T00:18:44Z","url":"https://dev.to/mishmanners/comment/1k4ni","interactionStatistic":[{"@type":"InteractionCounter","interactionType":"https://schema.org/LikeAction","userInteractionCount":2}],"parentItem":{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-808052"}}]},{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-809298","text":"\u003cp\u003eHi \u003ca class=\"mentioned-user\" href=\"https://dev.to/graciegregory\"\u003e@graciegregory\u003c/a\u003e\n \u0026amp; friends\u003cbr\u003e\nThis is an awesome idea!\u003cbr\u003e\nI contributed a github action to \"lint\" Podcast transcripts to the Changelog podcast, and wrote a blog post about it on the Changelog blog. Can I repurpose that here? Would it be a valid submission?\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLink on the changelog blog: \u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://changelog.com/posts/auto-improved-transcripts-with-github-actions\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003echangelog.com/posts/auto-improved-...\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Simey de Klerk","url":"https://dev.to/simeydk"},"datePublished":"2021-11-22T19:59:58Z","dateModified":"2021-11-22T19:59:58Z","url":"https://dev.to/simeydk/comment/1k14m","interactionStatistic":[{"@type":"InteractionCounter","interactionType":"https://schema.org/LikeAction","userInteractionCount":2}],"comment":[{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-811815","text":"\u003cp\u003eIf you created a new action or workflow, then definitely feel free to include 😄\u003c/p\u003e\n\n","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Michelle Duke","url":"https://dev.to/mishmanners"},"datePublished":"2021-11-29T00:18:06Z","dateModified":"2021-11-29T00:18:06Z","url":"https://dev.to/mishmanners/comment/1k4nh","interactionStatistic":[{"@type":"InteractionCounter","interactionType":"https://schema.org/LikeAction","userInteractionCount":1}],"parentItem":{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-809298"}}]},{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-802431","text":"\u003cp\u003eWill it be solo or team work(4 members)base hackathon?\u003c/p\u003e\n\n","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Atharva Shirdhankar","url":"https://dev.to/hey_atharva"},"datePublished":"2021-11-08T17:54:30Z","dateModified":"2021-11-08T17:54:30Z","url":"https://dev.to/hey_atharva/comment/1jh0j","interactionStatistic":[{"@type":"InteractionCounter","interactionType":"https://schema.org/LikeAction","userInteractionCount":2}],"comment":[{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-802470","text":"\u003cp\u003eSame question for me as well. Up!!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Rio Cantre","url":"https://dev.to/riocantre"},"datePublished":"2021-11-08T19:24:09Z","dateModified":"2021-11-08T19:24:09Z","url":"https://dev.to/riocantre/comment/1jh26","interactionStatistic":[{"@type":"InteractionCounter","interactionType":"https://schema.org/LikeAction","userInteractionCount":2}],"parentItem":{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-802431"}}]},{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-808044","text":"\u003cp\u003eHi \u003ca class=\"mentioned-user\" href=\"https://dev.to/blackgirlbytes\"\u003e@blackgirlbytes\u003c/a\u003e\n and \u003ca class=\"mentioned-user\" href=\"https://dev.to/mishmanners\"\u003e@mishmanners\u003c/a\u003e\n \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFirst of all, thank you a lot for organizing such a great hackathon, I really do appreciate it!\u003cbr\u003e\nOkay so now I have a doubt regarding the hackathon, the following paragraph is mentioned in the original post:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor this year’s hackathon, we’re encouraging participants to utilize existing GitHub Actions to create workflows that make sense in the real world. While you are free to create a new Action, the emphasis of this contest is to create practical and interesting solutions other developers can utilize to solve problems with open source.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDoes this mean that workflows that use \u003cstrong\u003eactions/Any_Action\u003c/strong\u003e in their jobs are preferred than others that use custom-made actions such as \u003cstrong\u003eshehab7osny/Any_Action\u003c/strong\u003e, right? or does it mean to stick to the Actions currently available on the GitHub Actions' marketplace without the need to develop new ones?\u003c/p\u003e\n\n","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Shehab Hosny","url":"https://dev.to/shehab7osny"},"datePublished":"2021-11-20T05:40:00Z","dateModified":"2021-11-20T12:55:40Z","url":"https://dev.to/shehab7osny/comment/1jp8g","interactionStatistic":[{"@type":"InteractionCounter","interactionType":"https://schema.org/LikeAction","userInteractionCount":1}],"comment":[{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-808838","text":"\u003cp\u003eThe idea is you'll need to either create an Action or workflow FROM an existing Action (preferred), or create a new Action entirely. Look at what's on the \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/marketplace?type=actions\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003eActions marketplace\u003c/a\u003e and build on one of those. Don't forget to write a blog post about it 😄\u003c/p\u003e\n\n","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Michelle Duke","url":"https://dev.to/mishmanners"},"datePublished":"2021-11-21T23:47:57Z","dateModified":"2021-11-25T04:18:30Z","url":"https://dev.to/mishmanners/comment/1k0d4","interactionStatistic":[{"@type":"InteractionCounter","interactionType":"https://schema.org/LikeAction","userInteractionCount":2}],"parentItem":{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-808044"}}]},{"@type":"Comment","@id":"#comment-802412","text":"\u003cp\u003eIf anyone has questions, I'm happy to help!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Rizèl Scarlett","url":"https://dev.to/blackgirlbytes"},"datePublished":"2021-11-08T17:26:30Z","dateModified":"2021-11-08T17:26:30Z","url":"https://dev.to/blackgirlbytes/comment/1jh00","interactionStatistic":[{"@type":"InteractionCounter","interactionType":"https://schema.org/LikeAction","userInteractionCount":4}]}]}}
